Package myAdapter

Class MapAdapter.KeySet

java.lang.Object
myAdapter.MapAdapter.MyAbstractCollection
myAdapter.MapAdapter.EntrySet
myAdapter.MapAdapter.KeySet
All Implemented Interfaces:
HCollection, HSet
Enclosing class:
MapAdapter
private class MapAdapter.KeySet
extends MapAdapter.EntrySet
Class which extends the EntrySet class overriding the methods depending on the type of the elements inside the set. Keys are unique in the map so the set can use directly the methods defined by the map.
Author:
Formaggio Alberto

      public boolean equals​(java.lang.Object o)
      Description copied from interface: HSet
      Compares the specified object with this set for equality. Returns true if the specified object is also a set, the two sets have the same size, and every member of the specified set is contained in this set (or equivalently, every member of this set is contained in the specified set). This definition ensures that the equals method works properly across different implementations of the set interface.
